title: Chair Backs, early 19th century
medium:
Medium: wool
Technique: Printed (stamped) by heated roller on wool velvet (baste plain weave with wool supplementary warp).
dimensions:
a. Warp: 52cm (20 1/2in.) Weft 42cm (16 1/2 in.).
b. Warp: 50 cm (19 5/8 in.). Weft: 40 cm (15 3/4in.)
description: Pair of chair backs with a stamped design of a floral bouquet on a field of twisted shapes. Design is in releif above the flattened background.
